<BaseLayout>
  <main class="prose mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p>Last updated: June 2026</p>
    <p>These Terms of Service govern your use of CampSoon, including www.campsoon.com and the CampSoon Chrome extension. By using CampSoon, you agree to these terms.</p>

    <h2>Service Description</h2>
    <p>CampSoon helps users monitor supported campsite reservation systems, starting with BC Parks, and receive alerts when matching campsite availability may appear. CampSoon is an independent availability monitoring and notification assistant. CampSoon is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or partnered with BC Parks or any official park reservation provider.</p>

    <h2>No Reservation Guarantee</h2>
    <p>Campsite availability can change quickly. CampSoon does not guarantee that any campsite will be available, that an alert will result in a completed booking, or that a reservation provider will accept or complete a reservation.</p>

    <h2>Accounts and User Responsibilities</h2>
    <p>You are responsible for keeping your CampSoon account secure, providing accurate information, complying with official park reservation provider rules, and using CampSoon only for lawful personal booking activity. You remain responsible for any official reservation provider account, reservation, cancellation, fee, tax, or policy that applies to your booking.</p>

    <h2>Point Packages and Billing</h2>
    <p>After public launch, CampSoon will sell one-time digital point packages. Point package purchases will be completed through Stripe Checkout inside the CampSoon Chrome extension. This website does not collect payments. Points are deducted only after CampSoon helps you successfully complete a campsite booking, and each successful booking uses exactly 1,000 points unless stated otherwise in the product.</p>

    <h2>Digital Delivery</h2>
    <p>CampSoon is delivered digitally through the Chrome extension and your CampSoon account after public release. No physical goods are shipped. Purchased points are normally added to your account after Stripe confirms successful payment.</p>

    <h2>Refunds</h2>
    <p>Refunds are governed by our <a href="/refund">Refund &amp; Billing Policy</a>. Unused point packages may be eligible for a refund within the stated refund window. Points used for successful bookings are final and non-refundable.</p>

    <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
    <p>You may not misuse CampSoon, attempt to bypass security controls, interfere with supported reservation systems, resell access without permission, reverse engineer non-public service components, or use CampSoon in a way that violates law or third-party platform rules.</p>

    <h2>Changes and Availability</h2>
    <p>We may update, suspend, or discontinue parts of CampSoon, including supported reservation providers, pricing, point rules, and features. We may also suspend accounts that create security, abuse, payment, or compliance risk.</p>

    <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, CampSoon is provided as-is and as available. CampSoon is not responsible for lost reservations, missed alerts, third-party provider outages, official reservation provider decisions, travel costs, campsite fees, or indirect damages.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about these terms can be sent to <strong>support@campsoon.com</strong>.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
